{"id": "22360", 
"title": "Bug 22360[Fonts] FontRegistry can not be instantiated using resources outside org.eclipse.jface.resource", 
"description": "Bug 22360[Fonts] FontRegistry can not be instantiated using resources outside org.eclipse.jface.resource. Therefore, all the resources being looked up are only relative to the location of the FontRegistry class in the org.eclipse.jface.resource path. It can be remedied if FontRegistry took a client class (or class loader) as an additional parameter in the constructor.", 
"OB": "", 
"EB": "", 
"SR": "When I try to create a FontRegistry instance for my application using the code snippet below, I get a MissingResourceException: com.company.product.MyClass

public void createFontRegistry() {
   FontRegistry fonts = new FontRegistry("com.company.product.fonts");
}

I do have a file called fonts.properties in my com/company/product/folder. However, if I try the following code instead:

com.company.product.MyClass

public void createFontRegistry() {
   ResourceBundle fonts = ResourceBundle.getBundle("com.company.product.fonts");
}

There is no exception.

Furthermore, if I create a complete copy of the FontRegistry class in my com.company.product package, then it works.

My guess is that this is a bug in the FontRegistry."}

